website.siteDescription: American Commercial Realty Corporation (ACR) provides acquisition, redevelopment, leasing, property management and construction management services to affiliate-owned properties as well as third parties. ACR currently oversees more than 2,000,000 square feet of commercial space in the eastern half of the United States. ACR combines national expertise and local knowledge to deliver favorable results for merchants and property owners.

items.title: Promenade Apartments
items.body:
COMMENTS

The Promenade Apartments are located at 1045 Cocoanut Avenue near downtown Sarasota, Sarasota Bay and the Sarasota cultural district. It is adjacent to a new center-city Publix Supermarket and Pharmacy. It is also situated within close proximity to local beaches, dining and shopping. The apartment building consists of a total of 29 apartments over three floors. The one bedroom – one bath units are all newly renovated with new appliances and a pass-thru kitchen with bar seating. There is an on-site laundromat, picnic and grilling areas in a friendly park-like setting along with an elevator. There is free parking onsite. Visit our website at: www.promenadeapartments.net

Your life, your place, you city… Live it well. Call 561-775-1300 for leasing information.

items.title: Paradise Cove
items.body:
COMMENTS

Paradise Cove Apartments are located in the Villages of Palm Beach Lakes at the Pointe Drive just off Palm Beach Lakes Boulevard. Located across the street from a large Publix shopping center with a variety of services and numerous offices. Paradise Cove is within close proximity to numerous shopping and dining alternatives. The new Palm Beach Outlet Mall is within 5 minutes. Available units include one bedroom – one bath and two bedroom – two bath units as well as two story – two bedroom – two bath townhomes. There is a complementary on-site fitness facility and a large swimming pool. I-95, the Florida Turnpike and Tri-Rail are all nearby for easy commuting.

Call 561-775-1300 for leasing information.

items.title: Oleander Residences
items.body:
COMMENTS

Just steps from the Atlantic Ocean and the Intracoastal Waterway sit the “Oleander Residences” in Palm Beach The property is midway between Bradley Place and North County Road and only two blocks from the island’s new Publix Supermarket and Pharmacy. Public access to the beach is available a short walk to the east. Palm Beach’s walking and bicycle path along Lake Worth with unobstructed views to West Palm Beach and its harbour are just to the west. The property is also a short walk from a myriad of restaurants and clubs.

The Oleander Residences are really a beauty and a tremendous investment……four 2 bedroom/2 bath units and four efficiency apartments. Great for rental, conversion to condos or for an estate or yacht owner to hold for their guests and staff.

The property is an impeccable complete redevelopment of a 1928 structure. Travertine floors, designer cabinetry, Silestone counters, high-end appliances including a Bosch refrigerator, stove, microwave & dishwasher are found in every unit. Individual A/C for each unit. Cove ceilings, crown molding and hi-hat lighting in every room. Units enjoy lots of light inside day and night!

The apartments have individual washer/dryers; studios share a laundry room. Paver courtyard and excellent curb appeal in a phenomenal location. Even the foundations were enhanced and the roof replaced.

Check out this link to the full gallery.

Call 561-775-1300 or info@AmComRealty.com for further information.

items.title: Cloisters of Lake Worth
items.body:
COMMENTS

Discover The Cloisters – a private urban retreat of gracious Mediterranean townhomes, inimitable luxury and the charming lifestyle of Lake Worth, Florida, a genteel small city endowed with world-class sophistication, sparkling waters and splendid beaches.

The Cloisters was designed to celebrate the nostalgia, sophistication and urban romance of historic Lake Worth and its charming downtown. Homes within the exclusive enclave reflect Mediterranean traditions of tile roofs, stucco exteriors and CBS construction.

The Cloisters is six blocks south of downtown’s dynamic arts and entertainment district, with its intriguing shops and elegant dining. The site is only a few moments from Bryant Park, the lake and the Intracoastal Waterway.

items.title: Beechmont (Anderson Office Park)
items.body:
COMMENTS

Anderson Office Park consists of five two-story suburban office buildings within an office park setting. Excellent visibility from Beechmont Avenue, ample free parking and easy access to I-275 lend to its prime location. It also has close proximity to downtown Cincinnati, the metropolitan airport and all regional business areas. The park is zoned for office and retail use making it attractive for a variety of users.

Anderson Office Park is situated in a market area including over 105,000 people within a five-mile radius. There is an average household income of over $95,000 within three miles.

Accessibility is outstanding with a signalized intersection on Beechmont Avenue coupled with pylon signage for key tenants. Anderson Office Park offers a prime location with numerous advantages.

items.title: Pinecrest Town Center
items.body:
COMMENTS

Pinecrest Town Center is located in the affluent Miami suburb of Pinecrest. The shopping center is surrounded by some of Miami's finest residential communities and the best public and private school systems in the area. The property enjoys 305 feet of frontage along South Dixie Highway (a 6-lane thoroughfare), a signalized entry for left turns in and out at SW 128th Street and ample free parking.

Shallow bay depths allow for maximum frontage for the retail bays. It is one of very few centers along the three-mile stretch of Dixie Highway between Dadeland and the Falls. In addition, the property includes a 4-story office building.

Major tenants include Get Smart Educational Superstore, EWM Realtors and Coldwell Banker. The shopping center is also a major culinary destination with such respected eateries as Anacapri Italian Restaurant, Sea Siam, Imlee Indian Bistro, Mitch’s Westside Bagel and Muffin Tin Restaurant. Pinecrest Town Center is an excellent mixed-use retail and office development serving Southeastern Miami-Dade County.

items.title: Mark Twain Village
items.body:
COMMENTS

Mark Twain Village is located in historic St. Charles, Missouri, at I-70’s first exit west of the Missouri River and minutes from downtown St. Charles. The center is distinguished by having one of Bass Pro Shops’ most successful stores and a newly renovated Gordmans as it’s anchors. Successful national and regional retailers and restaurateurs such as Gordman’s, Aldi, West Marine, Qdoba Mexican Grill, Buffalo Wild Wings, Club Fitness, and Texas Roadhouse.

With its outstanding visibility along I-70, which serves as the primary east-west route for metropolitan St. Louis, and excellent accessibility from a dedicated signalized entrance, Mark Twain Village attracts business from the entire region. Ameristar Casino, Lindenwod University, and the St. Charles Convention Center are within minutes of the center, making Mark Twain Village a destination for tourists as well as locals.

items.body:
COMMENTS

Westside South Shopping Center is a regional shopping center located on the heavily trafficked Westbank Expressway at Stumpf Boulevard in the city of Gretna, part of Jefferson Parish, a suburb of New Orleans, Louisiana. Westside South contains 277,763 square feet of first class retail space.

The center’s primary tenants are Home Depot, Rooms To Go, dd’s Discounts, Anna’s Linens and Finish Line. Rally’s, Mattress Firm, Taco Bell and Subway are located on freestanding outparcels. The center was originally built in 1983 but was renovated and expanded several times, most recently in 2005.

items.title: Buttermilk Crossing
items.body:
COMMENTS

Buttermilk Crossing is a 78,012 square foot community retail center located at 2301 – 2341 Buttermilk Crossing, approximately seven miles southwest of downtown Cincinnati, OH. The property is leased to a diverse roster of tenants, including Staples, Outback, Petco, The UPS Store, H&R Block, Heartland Dental, Domino’s Pizza and a mix of well-established local businesses. The property has recently completed a renovation of the center’s façade. The entire parking lot was recently restored while several sections were entirely replaced.

The property is well located immediately off of Interstate 71/75, which provides direct access to Cincinnati and the city’s suburban Kentucky market as well as the Cincinnati International Airport. The property is situated on a triangular parcel bordered by Buttermilk Pike (State Highway 371) and Grandview Drive adjacent to a Park n Ride transit center. The property has a signalized intersection at Buttermilk Pike where traffic counts exceed 35,000 vehicles per day.

Buttermilk Crossing boasts excellent visibility, easy access, and ample parking for its customers. It has a large pylon sign along Buttermilk Pike.

items.title: Cherry Tree
items.body:
COMMENTS

Cherry Tree Shopping Center is located along Washington Road (SR24) at the northwest corner at Cummings Lane in Washington, Illinois, a suburb of Peoria. Situated just east of Peoria, Washington is a popular destination for middle income and affluent residents of the Peoria area seeking space for their families, recreational opportunities and excellent schools.

Anchored by Kroger and Big R, Cherry Tree Shopping Center is a 112,000 square foot open air community shopping center (not including the separately owned Big R property) with a free-standing gasoline service station. The 55,000 square foot Kroger Supermarket includes a pharmacy with a drive-through window.

Cherry Tree has excellent visibility from both the roadways as well as excellent accessibility due to a fully signalized intersection with multiple curb cuts off both roads leading into the center. Cherry Tree Shopping center is a fixture in the Washington community as the dominant grocery-anchored property and the most desirable community/neighborhood space in the market.

items.title: Satilla Square
items.body:
COMMENTS

Satilla Square is a neighborhood shopping center with excellent visibility and ample parking. The property is located in Waycross, Georgia at Knight Avenue at the crossing of S. City Boulevard, in the retail section of Waycross, Georgia. The property is situated at a lighted intersection with a four way traffic signal and has excellent access points to the primary streets in both directions. The railway situated across Knight Avenue separates the property from Brunswick Highway, which is the dominant East/West corridor in the Waycross market. 

Join anchor tenants Dollar General Market, Big Lots and Rite Aid and coming soon - Harbor Freight Tools.

Satilla Square is a fixture in the Waycross market as a dominant anchored property in the general region offering some of the most desirable community/neighborhood space in the immediate trade area. There is an extensive rehab planned for Satilla Square.

items.title: Pinecrest Town Center
items.body:
COMMENTS

Pinecrest Town Center is located in the affluent Miami suburb of Pinecrest. The shopping center is surrounded by some of Miami's finest residential communities and the best public and private school systems in the area. The property enjoys 305 feet of frontage along South Dixie Highway (a 6-lane thoroughfare), a signalized entry for left turns in and out at SW 128th Street and ample free parking.

Shallow bay depths allow for maximum frontage for the retail bays. It is one of very few centers along the three-mile stretch of Dixie Highway between Dadeland and the Falls. In addition, the property includes a 4-story office building.

Major tenants include Get Smart Educational Superstore, EWM Realtors and Coldwell Banker. The shopping center is also a major culinary destination with such respected eateries as Anacapri Italian Restaurant, Sea Siam, Imlee Indian Bistro, Mitch’s Westside Bagel and Muffin Tin Restaurant. Pinecrest Town Center is an excellent mixed-use retail and office development serving Southeastern Miami-Dade County.

items.title: Naples South Plaza
items.body:
COMMENTS

Naples South Plaza is an 87,000 sq. ft. neighborhood shopping center located in Naples, Florida. Naples has consistently ranked as one of the fastest growing metropolitan areas in the nation, currently in the top five. The shopping center is located just 4 miles south of downtown Naples on US 41 at Rattlesnake Hammock Road. With easy access from all directions and a signalized intersection, the center boasts excellent visibility and accessibility for its tenants.

The Naples South market's retail potential has been underscored by the Publix Grocery's success at the Hammock Creek center directly across US 41 from the Naples South Plaza. In addition, Minto Communities is moving forward with The Isles of Collier Preserve, a new master-planned community having its principal entrance at our center. This large project, spread across 2,400 acres on the largest tract of undeveloped land west of US 41 in the county, will add 1,606 homes, 18 golf holes, 250 hotel rooms, and a new marina to the area. A sales center is slated to open Fall 2013, with the first models ready to tour in Fall 2014.

Major tenants at Naples South include Dollar General, Sears Outlet, Anthony's Ladies Apparel, Little Caesar's and The UPS Store.

items.title: Daytona Promenade
items.body:
COMMENTS

Centrally located in Daytona Beach at the NEC of Beville Road & Nova Road and within 5 miles of the famous Daytona International Speedway, is the 152,704 square foot Daytona Promenade shopping center. Beville Road is a primary east-west route, with direct I-95 and I-4 access to the west, and terminating at US 1 to the east. Nova Road is a primary north-south artery through Volusia County.

Daytona Promenade's major tenants include Sears Outlet, Bravo Supermarket, Planet Fitness, Family Dollar and PNC Bank. Other tenants include local businesses such as Metro PCS, Brighthouse Networks and many popular local restaurants.

The intersection of Beville Road & Nova Road has traffic counts of over 65,000 cars per day. The SWC corner of the intersection is occupied by a Wal-Mart Superstore and Sam's Wholesale Club. 3 available outparcels front Nova Road. In addition, several smaller shops are available. The center features excellent visibility along two major roadways, easy accessibility, and ample parking.

items.title: Beechmont Retail
items.body:
COMMENTS

The Property is a 90,957 square foot shopping center comprised of adjacent retail buildings situated across four separate centers in Anderson Township. The Property benefits from its location popular along Beechmont Avenue, the area’s strongest retail corridor, midway between Five Mile Road and I-275. Originally constructed in stages during the eighties and nineties, the Property is leased to more than 25 tenants, including Mercy Medical Systems, Dairy Queen, Subway, Ohio Pets, Sherwin Williams, the UPS Store, and a mix of well-established local businesses. It has been recently renovated.

The property is located in its entirety on the north side of Beechmont Avenue, east of Nagle Road. The Property boasts excellent visibility, easy access, and ample parking for its customers. There are two traffic signals providing access to the property. Anderson Township has one of the Cincinnati area’s best stock of housing and superior schools.

The shopping center is within a short distance of Home Depot, Target, Staples, and Macy's with many other big box retailers located within a two-mile radius of the property. Recent activity in the area has included the successful "de-malling" of Beechmont Mall (Anchored by Macy's), the addition of a new Super Kroger, several new automobile dealerships and restaurants.

items.title: Highland Square
items.body:
COMMENTS

Highland Square is the dominant shopping center in the North Jacksonville market; featuring over 277,000 square feet located on Dunn Avenue, one block west of I-95. The center is anchored by Publix Supermarkets, dd’s Discounts (a division of Ross Stores), Beall’s Outlet, Bailey’s Powerhouse Gym, Coco Beauty Superstore, Family Dollar and a CVS Pharmacy which is located on an outparcel. The balance of the occupied space contains a mix of regional, local and national tenants and truly caters to the dense surrounding market. The property is a fixture in the North Jacksonville community. Publix has been a tenant since 1973.

Access to the property is excellent as Highland occupies a full City block with traffic signals at both side streets and multiple entrances along Dunn Avenue. The center is high profile with excellent visibility and street exposure.

The area offers excellent nearby employment generators including the Jacksonville International Airport and the surrounding Tradeport, which is home to the new 1,700,000 square foot Amazon Fulfillment Center as well as the nearby Anheuser-Busch InBev brewery.
